  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Project Manager (Interior Fit-Out)</strong></p><p>We’re looking for a proactive and detail-oriented <strong>Project Manager (Interior Fit-Out) </strong>to ensure multiple projects run smoothly from concept to handover— <strong>on time, on budget, and to the required quality </strong>. This role will coordinate across designers, clients, contractors, and suppliers to manage scheduling, budgeting, procurement, and site execution.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><strong>Project planning & scheduling: </strong>Build and manage project schedules, milestones, and work plans from design development through completion</li><li><strong>Budget & cost control: </strong>Prepare and track budgets, manage cost reporting/variations, and ensure financial targets are met</li><li><strong>Team & resource management: </strong>Coordinate internal teams and external partners to ensure resources are allocated effectively</li><li><strong>Client management: </strong>Manage client expectations, provide regular updates, and respond promptly to requests and feedback</li><li><strong>Procurement coordination: </strong>Support sourcing, quotations, vendor coordination, lead times, and delivery schedules</li><li><strong>Quality control: </strong>Ensure drawings, materials, workmanship, and site deliverables meet required standards and specifications</li><li><strong>Risk, issue & change management: </strong>Identify risks early, drive issue resolution, and manage change orders with proper documentation and approvals</li><li><strong>Site execution & handover: </strong>Oversee site progress, coordinate contractors/subcontractors, manage inspections and snag lists, and ensure smooth handover and close-out</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
